tei:div.tei:p:
Ulrich did pass his final examination on the 19th; only in English was he tested orally. Unfortunately, that same evening he lay down in bed with bad stomach cramps;
early Friday (I returned from Leipzig on Thursday evening) his temperature was 37.6, midday 39.15, and in the evening 40.1. At 7 o'clock I called an ambulance to take him to the clinic, and at 8 o'clock they operated: appendix, with complications. His appendix had become abnormally long, already becoming attached to the pelvis, and somewhat inflamed. Yesterday and early today he was doing very poorly, this evening better. As a result, I will not go to Leipzig until tomorrow. Still, it was lucky that this episode did not occur between the written and oral examinations. He must stay in bed for two weeks. Walter and Peppel
are doing well. Now, I too have calmed down. Obviously he Ulrich cannot participate in the student fraternity and ball. –
